nodeMacSlotMap.name: nodeMacSlotMap
nodeMacSlotMap.description: Each Starbridge board is assigned a base physical address. The physical address for each port is then assigned as (baseAddress + portIndex - 1). The nodeMacSlotMap is a 5 element array of the hex coded base addresses contained in the node with empty slots assigned the base address of 00:00:00:00:00:00.

nodeColdBoot.name: nodeColdBoot
nodeColdBoot.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the node to reset which has the effect of resetting all the boards in the node.

nodeResetNvRam.name: nodeResetNvRam
nodeResetNvRam.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the node to reset the non-volatile RAM in each board in the node to default values.

nodeIpSlotTable.name: nodeIpSlotTable
nodeIpSlotTable.description: A table that contains the IP addresses of the boards in the node.

nodeIpSlotEntry.name: nodeIpSlotEntry
nodeIpSlotEntry.description: The IP address of one of the boards in the node.

nodeIpSlotIndex.name: nodeIpSlotIndex
nodeIpSlotIndex.description: The slot number in the node.

nodeIpSlotAddr.name: nodeIpSlotAddr
nodeIpSlotAddr.description: The IP address of the board in slot nodeIpSlotIndex.

boardIpAddr.name: boardIpAddr
boardIpAddr.description: The administratively assigned IP Address for this board.

boardReset.name: boardReset
boardReset.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the board to reset.

boardResetNvRam.name: boardResetNvRam
boardResetNvRam.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the non-volatile ram to be reset to their default values.

boardLedStatus.name: boardLedStatus
boardLedStatus.description: The returns 16 bits encoded as an integer that represent the LEDs found on the front panel of the System Management board and on internal LED displays on the Starbridge Board. The most significant bit represents the leftmost LED. PLEASE NOTE: If the bit is 1 it indicates that the LED is OFF. If the bit is 0 it indicates that the LED is ON.

boardSlotNum.name: boardSlotNum
boardSlotNum.description: The Galactica Chassis slot that this board resides in. The slots are numbered 0 thru n with 0 being the bottom slot.

boardResetCounts.name: boardResetCounts
boardResetCounts.description: The number of times the 68K processor on this board has reset since the last time the non-volatile ram has been reset to default values.

boardSnmpMibVersion.name: boardSnmpMibVersion
boardSnmpMibVersion.description: The version of the Artel Proprietary MIB supported by this board.

arcnetBoardsPresent.name: arcnetBoardsPresent
arcnetBoardsPresent.description: A 17 bit bit-significant register returned as an integer. If the bit is set there is a board in that slot. The least significant bit represents slot 0. The most significant bit represents the System Management board.

arcnetRxPkts.name: arcnetRxPkts
arcnetRxPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this board over the internal Arcnet interface.

arcnetTxPkts.name: arcnetTxPkts
arcnetTxPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted by this board over the internal Arcnet interface.

arcnetNakCnts.name: arcnetNakCnts
arcnetNakCnts.description: The number of Negative Acknowledgements received by this board over the internal Arcnet interface when attemting to transmit.

arcnetMyReconfigCounts.name: arcnetMyReconfigCounts
arcnetMyReconfigCounts.description: The number of times the internal Arcnet bus has been reconfigured by this board.

arcnetReconfigCounts.name: arcnetReconfigCounts
arcnetReconfigCounts.description: The total number of times the internal Arcnet bus has been reconfigured since powerup.

arcnetTrashedRxMsgs.name: arcnetTrashedRxMsgs
arcnetTrashedRxMsgs.description: The number of Arcnet receive messages that were discarded by this board.

arcnetTrashedTxMsgs.name: arcnetTrashedTxMsgs
arcnetTrashedTxMsgs.description: The number of Arcnet transmit messages that were discarded by this board.

bpStatsEnabled.name: bpStatsEnabled
bpStatsEnabled.description: The administrative state of this boards connection to the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

bpStatsRxPkts.name: bpStatsRxPkts
bpStatsRxPkts.description: Total number of packets received by this board from the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

bpStatsRxErrors.name: bpStatsRxErrors
bpStatsRxErrors.description: Number of received packets that were received from the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus that contained errors.

bpStatsTxPkts.name: bpStatsTxPkts
bpStatsTxPkts.description: Total number of packets transmitted by this board from the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

bpStatsTxErrors.name: bpStatsTxErrors
bpStatsTxErrors.description: Number of packets which could not be transmitted because the receiver board was busy.

bpStatsOperState.name: bpStatsOperState
bpStatsOperState.description: Operational state of this boards connection to the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

bpStatsInitialize.name: bpStatsInitialize
bpStatsInitialize.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the Backplane statistics to be cleared.

bpStatsTxQOverErrors.name: bpStatsTxQOverErrors
bpStatsTxQOverErrors.description: A count of the number of overflows of the backplane transmit queue.

bpStatsRxBusyTable.name: bpStatsRxBusyTable
bpStatsRxBusyTable.description: A table stored on each board (except System Managers) that counts the number of packets transmitted by this board across the backplane that had to be discarded because the receiving board was too busy.

bpStatsRxBusyTableEntry.name: bpStatsRxBusyTableEntry
bpStatsRxBusyTableEntry.description: An entry for another board in the node that counts the number of backplane packets from this board that the other board was too busy to receive.

bpStatsRxBusyTableIndex.name: bpStatsRxBusyTableIndex
bpStatsRxBusyTableIndex.description: The slot number of the receiving board.

bpStatsRxBusyTableErrors.name: bpStatsRxBusyTableErrors
bpStatsRxBusyTableErrors.description: A count of the number of backplane packets transmitted by this board to the board in slot bpStatsRxBusyTableIndex that the other board was too busy to receive.

restrictedTable.name: restrictedTable
restrictedTable.description: A table of physical addresses that are restricted from being bridged through this node. Filtering is done on both source and destination address.

restrictedEntry.name: restrictedEntry
restrictedEntry.description: Information needed to restrict a particular physical address.

restrictedAddr.name: restrictedAddr
restrictedAddr.description: The physical address to be restricted.

restrictedStatus.name: restrictedStatus
restrictedStatus.description: Indicates the state of the entry. Invalid items will be removed from the table.

bridgeAgeNow.name: bridgeAgeNow
bridgeAgeNow.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the forwarding database to be fully aged.

bridgeDot1dEnable.name: bridgeDot1dEnable
bridgeDot1dEnable.description: Enables and disables the IEE 802.1d Spanning Tree Protocol for the board.

bridgeDot1dResetDefaults.name: bridgeDot1dResetDefaults
bridgeDot1dResetDefaults.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the Spanning Tree objects to be reset to the default values.

bridgeResetPktSwCount.name: bridgeResetPktSwCount
bridgeResetPktSwCount.description: A count of the number of times the packet switching function has been reset.

bridgePktSwLastReset.name: bridgePktSwLastReset
bridgePktSwLastReset.description: The value of sysUpTime when the packet swtiching function was last reset.

bridgeResetStatic.name: bridgeResetStatic
bridgeResetStatic.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the static table to be cleared.

bridgeRestrictedReset.name: bridgeRestrictedReset
bridgeRestrictedReset.description: When queried, this object will always return the value 1. Setting this object to any value causes the restricted table to be cleared.

bridgeUdfTable.name: bridgeUdfTable
bridgeUdfTable.description: A table maintaining user defined filtering information on each port on the board.

bridgeUdfEntry.name: bridgeUdfEntry
bridgeUdfEntry.description: User defined filtering information maintained on a single port and filter.

bridgeUdfPortIndex.name: bridgeUdfPortIndex
bridgeUdfPortIndex.description: The port number on the board. Same as ifIndex.

bridgeUdfFilterIndex.name: bridgeUdfFilterIndex
bridgeUdfFilterIndex.description: The filter number for the port.

bridgeUdfState.name: bridgeUdfState
bridgeUdfState.description: The state of this filter. There are four states: disabled, filter, forward and count. In the disabled state, this filter is ignored. In the filter state, a packet matching this filter will be filtered or discarded. In the forward state, a packet matching this filter will be forwarded. In the count state, a packet matching this filter will increment the bridgeUdfMatchCounts and the filter will be ignored for filtering and forwarding purposes.

bridgeUdfComment.name: bridgeUdfComment
bridgeUdfComment.description: A comment field to describe this filter.

bridgeUdfMatchCounts.name: bridgeUdfMatchCounts
bridgeUdfMatchCounts.description: The number of packets that matched this filter when the bridgeUdfState was either filter, forward or count.

bridgeUdfInitMatchCount.name: bridgeUdfInitMatchCount
bridgeUdfInitMatchCount.description: When read this object always returns 1. When set to any value it will clear the bridgeUdfMatchCounts object for this port and filter.

bridgeUdfAddressType.name: bridgeUdfAddressType
bridgeUdfAddressType.description: Source indicates that the address portion of this filter is using the source MAC address. Destination indicates the address portion of this filter is using the destination MAC address.

bridgeUdfAddressValue.name: bridgeUdfAddressValue
bridgeUdfAddressValue.description: The data value used for comparison on the MAC address in the packet.

bridgeUdfAddressMask.name: bridgeUdfAddressMask
bridgeUdfAddressMask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the MAC address in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfAddressOperand.name: bridgeUdfAddressOperand
bridgeUdfAddressOperand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfAddressValue and the MAC address in the packet.

bridgeUdfTypeValue.name: bridgeUdfTypeValue
bridgeUdfTypeValue.description: The data value used for comparison on the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfTypeMask.name: bridgeUdfTypeMask
bridgeUdfTypeMask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the type field in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfTypeOperand.name: bridgeUdfTypeOperand
bridgeUdfTypeOperand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfTypeValue and the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset1Offset.name: bridgeUdfOffset1Offset
bridgeUdfOffset1Offset.description: The number of bytes from the start of the MAC header to the start of the data area in the packet to be used in the filter's comparison. This value must be divisible by 4.

bridgeUdfOffset1Value.name: bridgeUdfOffset1Value
bridgeUdfOffset1Value.description: The data value used for comparison on the offset1 field as specified by bridgeUdfOffset1Offset in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset1Mask.name: bridgeUdfOffset1Mask
bridgeUdfOffset1Mask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the offset1 field in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfOffset1Operand.name: bridgeUdfOffset1Operand
bridgeUdfOffset1Operand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfOffset1Value and the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset2Offset.name: bridgeUdfOffset2Offset
bridgeUdfOffset2Offset.description: The number of bytes from the start of the MAC header to the start of the data area in the packet to be used in the filter's comparison. This value must be divisible by 4.

bridgeUdfOffset2Value.name: bridgeUdfOffset2Value
bridgeUdfOffset2Value.description: The data value used for comparison on the offset1 field as specified by bridgeUdfOffset2Offset in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset2Mask.name: bridgeUdfOffset2Mask
bridgeUdfOffset2Mask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the offset2 field in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfOffset2Operand.name: bridgeUdfOffset2Operand
bridgeUdfOffset2Operand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfOffset2Value and the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset3Offset.name: bridgeUdfOffset3Offset
bridgeUdfOffset3Offset.description: The number of bytes from the start of the MAC header to the start of the data area in the packet to be used in the filter's comparison. This value must be divisible by 4.

bridgeUdfOffset3Value.name: bridgeUdfOffset3Value
bridgeUdfOffset3Value.description: The data value used for comparison on the offset1 field as specified by bridgeUdfOffset3Offset in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset3Mask.name: bridgeUdfOffset3Mask
bridgeUdfOffset3Mask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the offset3 field in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfOffset3Operand.name: bridgeUdfOffset3Operand
bridgeUdfOffset3Operand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfOffset3Value and the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset4Offset.name: bridgeUdfOffset4Offset
bridgeUdfOffset4Offset.description: The number of bytes from the start of the MAC header to the start of the data area in the packet to be used in the filter's comparison. This value must be divisible by 4.

bridgeUdfOffset4Value.name: bridgeUdfOffset4Value
bridgeUdfOffset4Value.description: The data value used for comparison on the offset1 field as specified by bridgeUdfOffset4Offset in the packet.

bridgeUdfOffset4Mask.name: bridgeUdfOffset4Mask
bridgeUdfOffset4Mask.description: The value used to mask off the data value used for comparison on the offset4 field in the packet. Don't care bits are zero.

bridgeUdfOffset4Operand.name: bridgeUdfOffset4Operand
bridgeUdfOffset4Operand.description: The operand used in the comparison of the bridgeUdfOffset4Value and the type field in the packet.

bridgeUdfInitCountTable.name: bridgeUdfInitCountTable
bridgeUdfInitCountTable.description: A table used to clear all of a port's bridgeUdfMatchCounts.

bridgeUdfInitCountEntry.name: bridgeUdfInitCountEntry
bridgeUdfInitCountEntry.description: A table entry used to clear all of a port's bridgeUdfMatchCounts.

bridgeUdfCountPortIndex.name: bridgeUdfCountPortIndex
bridgeUdfCountPortIndex.description: The port number on the board. Same as ifIndex.

bridgeUdfCountInitMatchCount.name: bridgeUdfCountInitMatchCount
bridgeUdfCountInitMatchCount.description: When read this object always returns 1. When set to any value it will clear all of the bridgeUdfMatchCounts objects for this port.

bridgePortGroupEnable.name: bridgePortGroupEnable
bridgePortGroupEnable.description: Enables and disables all Port Group filtering for the node.

bridgePortGroupTable.name: bridgePortGroupTable
bridgePortGroupTable.description: A table containing the port group information on each port and group in the node.

bridgePortGroupEntry.name: bridgePortGroupEntry
bridgePortGroupEntry.description: Port group information maintained on a single port and group.

bridgePortGroupTablePortIndex.name: bridgePortGroupTablePortIndex
bridgePortGroupTablePortIndex.description: The port number in the node.

bridgePortGroupTableGroupIndex.name: bridgePortGroupTableGroupIndex
bridgePortGroupTableGroupIndex.description: The group number in the node.

bridgePortGroupTableEnable.name: bridgePortGroupTableEnable
bridgePortGroupTableEnable.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. enable(1) - This port is currently contained in this group. disable(2) - This port is not currently contained in this group.

bridgePortGroupPortTable.name: bridgePortGroupPortTable
bridgePortGroupPortTable.description: A table containing the port group information as readable strings on each port on the board.

bridgePortGroupPortEntry.name: bridgePortGroupPortEntry
bridgePortGroupPortEntry.description: Port group information maintained on a single port.

bridgePortGroupPortIndex.name: bridgePortGroupPortIndex
bridgePortGroupPortIndex.description: The port number on the board. Same as ifIndex.

bridgePortGroupPortDisplayString.name: bridgePortGroupPortDisplayString
bridgePortGroupPortDisplayString.description: A readable string that contains all of the port groups that this port is a member of.

bridgePortGroupGroupTable.name: bridgePortGroupGroupTable
bridgePortGroupGroupTable.description: A table maintaining the port group information for each group on the node.

bridgePortGroupGroupEntry.name: bridgePortGroupGroupEntry
bridgePortGroupGroupEntry.description: Port group information maintained on a single port group.

bridgePortGroupGroupIndex.name: bridgePortGroupGroupIndex
bridgePortGroupGroupIndex.description: The group number on the node.

bridgePortGroupGroupPortMap.name: bridgePortGroupGroupPortMap
bridgePortGroupGroupPortMap.description: The set of ports which are members of this group. Packets can only be forwarded to ports in the same port group(s) as the port on which the packet was received. A port can be in multiple port groups. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8 on board 1, the second octet specifying ports 1 through 8 on board 2, etc. Within each octet the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

bridgePortGroupGroupComment.name: bridgePortGroupGroupComment
bridgePortGroupGroupComment.description: A readable string that contains all of the port groups that this port is a member of.

bridgeAddrFilterTable.name: bridgeAddrFilterTable
bridgeAddrFilterTable.description: A table that contains information about MAC addresses for which the node has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

bridgeAddrFilterEntry.name: bridgeAddrFilterEntry
bridgeAddrFilterEntry.description: Address filtering information maintained on a block of 100 entries in the node's filtering database.

bridgeAddrFilterBlockIndex.name: bridgeAddrFilterBlockIndex
bridgeAddrFilterBlockIndex.description: Block number for this entry. Each block holds information on 100 entry locations into the node's address filtering database.

bridgeAddrFilterBlockData.name: bridgeAddrFilterBlockData
bridgeAddrFilterBlockData.description: There will be 100 address entries returned. Each address entry contains the following data: ENTRY NUMBER: 2 octets - The physical entry into the node's address filtering database for this address. MAC ADDRESS: 6 octets - The MAC address for this entry. ENTRY TYPE: 1 octet - The type of entry can be one of the following: invalid(1) : this entry is not valid. learned(2) : the value of the PORT and SLOT was learned, and is being used. static(3) : the address is in the dot1dStaticTable with the instance of the MAC address. restrict(4) : the address is in the restrictedTable with the instance of the MAC address. spantree(5) : the address is the spanning tree group address. self(6) : The address is one of the bridge's addresses. The SLOT indicates which of the node's boards has this address. SLOT: 1 octet - If 'learned' the slot number of the board on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the MAC address has been seen. If 'self' the slot number of the board with that MAC address. Else a value of '0' indicating that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this MAC address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). PORT: 1 octet - If 'learned' the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the MAC address has been seen. Else a value of '0' indicating that the bridge does have some forwarding/ filtering information about this MAC address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). AGE: 1 octet - If 'learned' the value of the AGE flag: invalid(1) : not valid for this entry. notaged(2) : the MAC address has not been aged. onceaged(3) : The MAC address has been aged once. It will be removed from the database the next time the aging process executes unless a packet with the MAC address in the source address field is received.

bridgedot1dTpFdbTable.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbTable
bridgedot1dTpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about MAC addresses for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame. This table is an extension of the dot1dTpFdbTable.

bridgedot1dTpFdbEntry.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbEntry
bridgedot1dTpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

bridgedot1dTpFdbAddress.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbAddress
bridgedot1dTpFdbAddress.description: A MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information. Same as dot1dTpFdbAddress.

bridgedot1dTpFdbSlot.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbSlot
bridgedot1dTpFdbSlot.description: If bridgeDot1dTpFdbStatus is 'learned' then the slot number of the board on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the MAC address has been seen. If 'self' the slot number of the board with that MAC address. Else a value of '0' indicating that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this MAC address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable).

bridgedot1dTpFdbPort.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbPort
bridgedot1dTpFdbPort.description: If bridgeDot1dTpFdbStatus is 'learned' then the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the MAC address has been seen. Else a value of '0' indicating that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this MAC address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable).

bridgedot1dTpFdbStatus.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbStatus
bridgedot1dTpFdbStatus.description: The type of entry can be one of the following: invalid(1) : This entry is not valid. learned(2) : The value of the PORT and SLOT was learned, and is being used. static(3) : The address is in the dot1dStaticTable with the instance of the MAC address. restrict(4) : The address is in the restrictedTable with the instance of the MAC address. spantree(5) : The address is the spanning tree group address. self(6) : The address is one of the bridge's addresses. The port indicates which of the node's boards has this address.

bridgedot1dTpFdbAge.name: bridgedot1dTpFdbAge
bridgedot1dTpFdbAge.description: If the bridgedot1dTpFdbStatus is 'learned' then the value of the AGE flag is: invalid(1) : Not valid for this entry. notaged(2) : The MAC address has not been aged. onceaged(3) : The MAC address has been aged once. It will be removed from the database the next time the aging process executes unless a packet with the MAC address in the source address field is received.

smCfgManufactureDate.name: smCfgManufactureDate
smCfgManufactureDate.description: The manufacture date of this System Management board.

smCfgHardwareRev.name: smCfgHardwareRev
smCfgHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision number of this System Management board.

smCfgSerialNumber.name: smCfgSerialNumber
smCfgSerialNumber.description: The serial number of this System Management board.

smCfgMacAddr.name: smCfgMacAddr
smCfgMacAddr.description: The physical address of this System Management board.

smCfgFlashMemSize.name: smCfgFlashMemSize
smCfgFlashMemSize.description: Number of bytes of flash memory on this System Management board.

smCfg68kRamSize.name: smCfg68kRamSize
smCfg68kRamSize.description: Management software RAM size on this System Management board.

smCfgBootRev.name: smCfgBootRev
smCfgBootRev.description: Revision number and date of the boot software on this System Management board.

smCfg68kRev.name: smCfg68kRev
smCfg68kRev.description: Revision number and date of the management software on this System Management board.

smCfgModulePartNumber.name: smCfgModulePartNumber
smCfgModulePartNumber.description: The Artel part number for this System Management module.

smCfgModuleSerialNumber.name: smCfgModuleSerialNumber
smCfgModuleSerialNumber.description: The Artel serial number for this System Management module.

smCfgStoreFlashRev.name: smCfgStoreFlashRev
smCfgStoreFlashRev.description: The version number of the software loaded in the store flash memory bank on this System Management board.

smCfgExecFlashRev.name: smCfgExecFlashRev
smCfgExecFlashRev.description: The version number of the software loaded in the executable flash memory bank on this System Management board.

smBpType.name: smBpType
smBpType.description: The type of Galactica 1 gigabit GBus on this node.

smBpArbTimer.name: smBpArbTimer
smBpArbTimer.description: The timeout period used to switch from asyncronous packets to syncronous packets.

smBpMaxPktSize.name: smBpMaxPktSize
smBpMaxPktSize.description: The maximum packet size transmitted over the node's Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

smBpAsyncSlotsEnb.name: smBpAsyncSlotsEnb
smBpAsyncSlotsEnb.description: A bit string returned as an integer that indicates which boards are asynchronous. The least significant bit represents the board in slot 0.

smBpSyncSlotsEnb.name: smBpSyncSlotsEnb
smBpSyncSlotsEnb.description: A bit string returned as an integer that indicates which boards are synchronous. The least significant bit represents the board in slot 0.

smBpUtilization.name: smBpUtilization
smBpUtilization.description: The current percentage of Galactica 1 gigabit GBus utilization.

smBpTable.name: smBpTable
smBpTable.description: A table maintaining state information on each board in the node.

smBpEntry.name: smBpEntry
smBpEntry.description: Information maintained on a single board.

smBpIndex.name: smBpIndex
smBpIndex.description: The slot number of the board.

smBpTableEnable.name: smBpTableEnable
smBpTableEnable.description: The current operational state of the board as viewed by the System Management board.

smBpTableJabber.name: smBpTableJabber
smBpTableJabber.description: True indicates that the board transmitted a packet that was larger than the maximum packet size and was disabled from the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus by the System Management board. This state will not be automatically re-set. The board cannot be re-enabled until manual intervention is taken by setting the smBpTableClearJabber object as defined below.

smBpTableClearJabber.name: smBpTableClearJabber
smBpTableClearJabber.description: When read this object always returns 1. When set to any value, the System Manager will clear the smBpTableJabber object allowing the board to be re-enabled onto the Galactica 1 gigabit GBus.

smSupplyPresent.name: smSupplyPresent
smSupplyPresent.description: A bit string returned as an integer that represents the presence of the power supplies. The lease significant bit represents power supply 1 which the leftmost power supply.

smSupplyType.name: smSupplyType
smSupplyType.description: A bit string returned as an integer that indicates the type of power supply present. Two bits are assigned to each power supply with the 2 least significant bits representing power supply 1. The bits are encoded such that: 00 invalid 01 No supply present 10 DC supply 11 AC supply

smSupplyAcOk.name: smSupplyAcOk
smSupplyAcOk.description: A bit string returned as an integer that indicates the status of the AC power units. The least significant bit represents power supply 1.

smSupplyDcOk.name: smSupplyDcOk
smSupplyDcOk.description: A bit string returned as an integer that indicates the status of the DC power units. The least significant bit represents power supply 1.

smSupplyTable.name: smSupplyTable
smSupplyTable.description: A table of strings describing the status of the chassis power supplies.

smSupplyTableEntry.name: smSupplyTableEntry
smSupplyTableEntry.description: The status of one power supply in the chassis.

smSupplyTableIndex.name: smSupplyTableIndex
smSupplyTableIndex.description: The number of the power supply in the chassis, numbered from left to right.

smSupplyTableStatus.name: smSupplyTableStatus
smSupplyTableStatus.description: A text description of the status of the power supply. One of: 'NOT PRESENT', 'OFF', 'ON' or 'FAILURE'.

smModemType.name: smModemType
smModemType.description: The modem type present on the node's System Management board.

smModemCallBackEnable.name: smModemCallBackEnable
smModemCallBackEnable.description: Enables and disables the call-back feature of the modem. If enabled the modem will answer a call, then hang up and dial the number in smModemCallBackNumber. If disabled the modem will not hang up on any calls.

smModemCallBackNumber.name: smModemCallBackNumber
smModemCallBackNumber.description: A Hayes style dial string that the internal modem uses if call-back is enabled. The string should not contain the 'ATD' characters, but a leading 'P' may be used to initiate pulse dialing if needed.

sbCfgManufactureDate.name: sbCfgManufactureDate
sbCfgManufactureDate.description: The manufacture date of this Starbridge board.

sbCfgHardwareRev.name: sbCfgHardwareRev
sbCfgHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision number of this Starbridge board.

sbCfgSerialNumber.name: sbCfgSerialNumber
sbCfgSerialNumber.description: The serial number of this Starbridge board.

sbCfgNumberIfBoards.name: sbCfgNumberIfBoards
sbCfgNumberIfBoards.description: The number of interface cards on this module.

sbCfgIfBd1Type.name: sbCfgIfBd1Type
sbCfgIfBd1Type.description: The interface type of interface card 1.

sbCfgIfBd1Rev.name: sbCfgIfBd1Rev
sbCfgIfBd1Rev.description: The hardware revision number of interface card 1.

sbCfgIfBd1SerialNum.name: sbCfgIfBd1SerialNum
sbCfgIfBd1SerialNum.description: The serial number of interface card 1.

sbCfgIfBd1NumPorts.name: sbCfgIfBd1NumPorts
sbCfgIfBd1NumPorts.description: The number of ports contained on interface card 1.

sbCfgIfBd2Type.name: sbCfgIfBd2Type
sbCfgIfBd2Type.description: The interface type of interface card 2.

sbCfgIfBd2Rev.name: sbCfgIfBd2Rev
